\begin{hxmodule2}{DisplayLogos}{displays the product and company logos in the viewer}
\hxpackname{amira}
\hxlabel{DisplayLogos}

\begin{hxdescription} 

This module displays the product logo (\ProductName) as well as the 
\CompanyName logo in the viewer window. In order 
to do this, a specific Open Inventor file is loaded that contains 
transparent raster graphics files. The user can choose between 
different versions, each having a different size.

Internally, the {\it DisplayLogos} script object loads the Open Inventor
file and creates an \hxref{HxIvDisplay}{IvDisplay} module. Choose 
{\it Pool/Show All} to see these hidden modules in the Pool.

\end{hxdescription}

\begin{hxports}
\hxlabel{DisplayLogos_logoHeight}
\hxport{Logo height}\\
\hximage{DisplayLogos_logoHeight}\\
Choose the desired size of the logo.
\end{hxports}

\begin{hxsection}{Related Topics}
The resource file for this module also defines the global Tcl command
\begin{quote}
{\tt createLogos [size]}
\end{quote}
to easily display the logos. For convenience, this command hides the 
newly created {\it DisplayLogos} module in the Pool. The optional
argument {\tt size} allows you to specify the size of the logo, where 
only those values offered in the module's {\it Logo height} port are 
valid.
\end{hxsection}

\end{hxmodule2}
